  <scopecontent id="aspace_7bfcb50ead72fa94ff39206c0e231bb5">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>The collection contains information about the student body, activism, alcohol, drugs, and foreign students on campus. Materials include newspaper clippings, pictures, correspondence, reports, statistics, and academic and student papers.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <custodhist id="aspace_21714101cf564303e5ea5f8cec341e0a">
    <head>Custodial History</head>
<p>The "Student Body" collection was created by Russell Miller, possibly while preparing "Light on the Hill," his history of Tufts College. The material was assembled from various departments. No attempt has been made to restore the original order of this material.</p>  </custodhist>
